<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALM LATITUDES: L.A. SPEAK; ART GALLERESE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark Ehrman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carrie Nation gallery: n . a nonalcoholic reception.  
</P>
<P>
 Chippendale Picasso: n . a male artist who earns a solo show because of his 
bod, not his art. 
</P>
<P>
 Last Supper: n . a show that draws only 12 or so people. 
</P>
<P>
 list lizard: n . someone who asks to see the price list but has no intention 
of buying. "Don't count on that list lizard . He's trying to impress his date." 
</P>
<P>
 Man Ray's violin: n . an attractive woman; named after Man Ray's photo of a 
woman's backside painted like a violin. "Forget the art. Check out Man Ray's 
violin over by the bar." 
</P>
<P>
 munchie circuit: n . the free food and booze at gallery openings. "Before I 
made it big, I just lived off the munchie circuit. " 
</P>
<P>
 Norton anthology: n . a group show aimed at a particularly free-spending art 
collector. Named after the Norton literary anthologies and art patrons and 
software tycoons Peter and Eileen Norton. 
</P>
<P>
 red dot heaven: n . a sellout show. A red dot placed next to the work and on 
the price list indicates that the piece has been sold. Mark Ehrman 
</P>
</TEXT>
