<TEXT>
<P>
 TRUMPET WORKS: Sergei Nakarjakov, trumpet; Alexander Markovich, piano. Teldec 
9031-77705-2. Nakarjakov -- 15 years old in 1992 when he made this recording -- 
presents surprisingly mature technique and interpretation in a potpourri of 
idiomatic works.Many of these selections highlight virtuosity over musical 
content: Rimsky-Korsakov's "Flight of the Bumblebee"; Dinicu's "Hora Staccato" 
and Jean-Baptiste Arban's standard, "The Carnival of Venice," all provide 
acrobatic flights deftly assayed by this Russian-born Israeli. Nevertheless, 
the trumpeter tempers fiery showmanship with a canny sense of style. He proves 
himself as comfortable with jazz-influenced pieces as he seems with 
19th-Century encore archetypes. He also turns in a convincing, sometimes 
compelling performance of a sonatina by the French composer Jeanine Rueff. 
Markovich accompanies with appropriate flair, empathy and technical finesse. 
SUSAN BLISS 
