<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUNS HAVE NO PLACE IN A HEALTHY LIFESTYLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It is possible The Times would appreciate thanks and a positive reaction to 
the new Life & Style section. 
</P>
<P>
 However, as I turned to this much heralded debut (April 25), I was immediately 
faced with the image of "Terminator II," complete with automatic weapon at the 
ready. 
</P>
<P>
 Must we be propagandized into thinking violence is popular and fashionable? 
Marginal behavior is so easily influenced. 
</P>
<P>
 It is not only the duty of all concerned of our citizenry, but especially the 
news media, movies and television, to bear some responsibility toward the 
Herculean burden of establishing the aura of a more secure, sane society if we 
hope to survive as a nation. 
</P>
<P>
 STAN CAPLAN 
</P>
<P>
 Canoga Park 
</P>
