<P>
CONSUMER CREDIT RISES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Consumer credit shot up 11.1% at an annual rate in March, the Federal Reserve 
said Friday. It was the biggest jump in three months as shoppers escaped the 
clutches of winter and enjoyed an early Easter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
