<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; YEMEN; NORTHERN TROOPS ADVANCE ON ADEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Guns boomed east of Aden as northern troops advanced on the southern 
stronghold on the third day of civil war.Foreigners terrorized by the 
escalating bloodshed fled Aden and the capital, Sana. The northerners have been 
trying to cut off access to vital oil fields and installations controlled by 
the southerners. Conservative North Yemen merged with socialist South Yemen in 
May, 1990, to form the Arab world's youngest republic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
