3 MEN SERIOUSLY INJURED WHEN CAR SLAMS INTO TREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three men were seriously injured early Saturday when their car veered across 
Brookhurst Street and struck a tree, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, Adrian Charles Muldrew, 36, of Fountain Valley, faces charges of 
suspicion of possession of amphetamines and driving under the influence of 
alcohol or drugs after the 2:45 a.m. accident, said Fountain Valley police Sgt. 
Keith Levin. 
</P>
<P>
 Muldrew was listed in critical but stable condition at Western Medical Center 
in Santa Ana with hip and skull injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Muldrew's passengers -- Jeffrey P. Tucker, 37, of Fountain Valley, and Steven 
J. McCleave, 35 of Balboa -- were also badly hurt. Tucker, who was riding in 
the front passenger seat, was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange, where he 
was listed in critical condition with head trauma, internal injuries and a 
pelvic fracture. 
</P>
<P>
 McCleave, who was in the back seat, was taken to Western Medical Center in 
Santa Ana with a broken leg. He was listed in stable condition Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Muldrew was driving his Nissan 240 SX southbound on Brookhurst at 
approximately 80 m.p.h. when the car veered across the center line just past 
Talbert Avenue and struck a large pine tree, a Fountain Valley Fire Department 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 It took firefighters 25 minutes to pull Muldrew from the mangled car, he said. 
</P>
