<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAL POLY POMONA WOMEN DEFEAT DAVIS, ADVANCE TO TENNIS FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-ranked Cal Poly Pomona defeated UC Davis, 5-3, to advance to the finals of 
the NCAA Division II women's tennis tournament at the Industry Hills Sheraton 
Resort Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Pomona (21-1-1) will play North Florida (24-3) for the championship at noon 
today.North Florida beat fourth-seeded Grand Canyon, 6-2, in the other 
semifinal.  
</P>
<P>
 The Broncos, who can win their fifth title and their third in four years, were 
seeded third despite being the top team in the Division II polls. North Florida 
was seeded No. 1, defending champion Davis No. 2.  
</P>
<P>
 Davis and Pomona were tied, 3-3, after singles play. But Pomona won the first 
two doubles matches to win. Twins Bee and Beam Amesbutr teamed up for one of 
Pomona's doubles victories. It was the first time they played as a team this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis (14-9) will play Grand Canyon (20-4) at 1:30 for third place. 
</P>
