<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAME OF THE WEEK; MONTENEGRO IS DOUBLE THREAT FOR SOUTH GATE; BASEBALL: HE 
THROWS A TWO-HITTER IN HIS PITCHING DEBUT AND ACCOUNTS FOR TWO RUNS IN A 3-0 
VICTORY OVER ROOSEVELT. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROY JURGENS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jose Montenegro was a one-man wrecking crew. 
</P>
<P>
 The South Gate shortstop-catcher made his first pitching appearance of the 
season an impressive one, fanning six batters and tossing a two-hit, 3-0 
victory over Roosevelt.The Eastern League make-up game was Monday at Evergreen 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Montenegro also provided all the offense the Rams would need, doubling twice, 
driving in a run and scoring a run. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams pounded eight hits off Roosevelt starter Fernie Garcia, who suffered 
his first defeat of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia struck out eight batters, but had trouble finding the strike zone, 
walking six.  
</P>
<P>
 The Roughriders squandered the few scoring opportunities they received, 
stranding a runner on third with no outs in the first and fourth innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Brothers Alex and Juan Carlos Rodriguez managed the only hits for the 
Roughriders, with a double apiece. 
</P>
<P>
 Six of the Rams' eight hits were singles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
