<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL ROUNDUP; FREMONT WINS, 7-3, ON MONTERROSA TRIPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TONY JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fremont 7, South Gate 3 -- Designated hitter Rinaldo Monterrosa's two-out 
three-run triple in the bottom of the fifth was the difference in the 
Pathfinders' Southeastern Conference upset victory Thursday at home. Monterrosa 
went two-for-two with one walk and three RBIs in the game.South Gate pitcher 
Rick Alcantar went three-for-three with one RBI and scored two of the Rams' 
three runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell 9, Jefferson 3 -- Catcher Jose Lopez went three-for-three with two RBIs 
in a Southeastern Conference game Thursday at Bell, for the Eagles' 10th 
consecutive win. Lopez also threw out three Jefferson runners trying to steal 
second. First baseman Val Beltran was two-for-three with two RBIs for Bell. 
</P>
<P>
 Manual Arts 5, Los Angeles 3 -- Manual Arts pitcher Jesus Rosales tossed a 
three-hitter and struck out six batters Wednesday at Harvard Park as the 
Toilers remained undefeated in Metro League play. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles took a 1-0 lead in the first inning when left fielder Roger Valle 
scored on a single by catcher George Guzman. But Manual Arts pulled ahead 3-1 
when catcher Louie Gallarde hit a two-run triple and then scored on a passed 
ball. 
</P>
<P>
 The Toilers padded their lead in the third when Gallardo walked, advanced to 
third on consecutive passed balls and scored on a fielder's choice. The Romans 
closed the gap, 4-3, in the sixth on Archie Underwood's two-run homer. 
</P>
<P>
 Manual Arts added an insurance run in the bottom of the sixth on an RBI single 
by right fielder Mario Arambula. TONY JONES 
</P>
