<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOY, 6, DIES AFTER BEING EJECTED FROM HIS FATHER'S CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 6-year-old boy was killed Saturday in a crash involving two suspected drunk 
drivers, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy was a passenger in a car driven by his father, Pedro Guzman, 34, of 
North Hollywood, police said.Guzman's car crashed into a pickup driven by 
Gilbert Ramirez, 24, of Sun Valley, said Los Angeles Police Officer Frank Zdroy 
of Valley Traffic Division. 
</P>
<P>
 According to police, the boy was not wearing a seat belt in the 6:30 p.m. 
crash and was ejected from the car. Police did not give the boy's name. 
</P>
<P>
 Guzman swerved into oncoming lanes and hit Ramirez's truck on Riverton Avenue 
near Arminta Street, Zdroy said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both men were arrested on suspicion of felony drunk driving, Zdroy said. 
JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
