<HEADLINE>
<P>
N.Y. OFFICER, 2 OTHERS ARRESTED IN BURBANK RAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A New York City narcotics detective and two friends have been arrested in the 
rape of a 26-year-old woman they met at a local nightclub, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 New York Police Detective Thomas John Kid, 27; John James Calimano, 27, and 
Richard Daniel Haime, 28, all of New York City, were arrested Thursday by 
Burbank detectives as the three men stood in line at NBC Studios for a taping 
of the Jay Leno Show. 
</P>
<P>
 The Burbank woman told police that she was raped early Thursday morning after 
she asked the men for a ride home from a popular dance spot. 
</P>
<P>
 The three men are each charged with rape, forced oral copulation and false 
imprisonment and are being held in lieu of $1-million bail each at Burbank City 
Jail. 
</P>
<P>
 According to police, the three men were vacationing in California and staying 
at a local motel. They checked out soon after the alleged sexual assault and 
checked into another motel in Orange County, returning to Burbank to attend the 
Leno taping, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The New York Police Department has temporarily suspended the detective, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The three are scheduled to be arraigned in Burbank Municipal Court on Monday. 
JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
