<P>
BRIEFLY; CHARITY: ACTIVIST BRAND TO BE HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sybil Brand, widely known for her efforts to improve conditions for women and 
juvenile prisoners, will be honored at a luncheon May 15 at the 
</P>
<P>
 Bel Age Hotel in West Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 Brand, who turns 92 today, is slated to receive a humanitarian award from the 
Los Angeles branch of the Women's American ORT, a nonprofit organization that 
supports vocational and technical training around the world. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission to the luncheon is $50. The proceeds will be used to establish a 
Sybil Brand Scholarship Fund at the Los Angeles ORT Technical Institute. 
Information: (213) 655-2911 or (310) 556-1466. Education: Open Enrollment 
Offered 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica/Malibu Unified School District has implemented an open enrollment 
policy for the first time. Until May 25, parents who live in the district can 
apply to enroll their child in any school in the district. 
</P>
<P>
 Approval will be subject to available space and the district's ethnic 
guidelines. A ratio of 70% whites to 30% minority students constitutes a 
racially balanced district. Also, families who live within the neighborhood 
boundaries of a particular school will be given preference to enroll at that 
school. 
</P>
<P>
 Open enrollment applications are available at all Santa Monica/Malibu schools, 
and at the district office, 1651 16th St., Santa Monica. Information: (310) 
450-8338. Business: Seminar on Workers' Comp 
</P>
<P>
 A Santa Monica insurance brokerage firm is offering a free seminar Monday 
featuring specialists in the managed-care approach to workers' compensation. 
</P>
<P>
 Andreini & Co. invites representatives from area businesses to attend. The 
seminar is scheduled for 8:30 a.m. at the Doubletree Hotel, 1401 Admiralty Way, 
Marina del Rey. Presenters will include representatives of Blue Cross, 
FHP/Great States and Foundation Health. 
</P>
