<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: LEIMERT PARK; EARTHQUAKE AID CENTER TO OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Next week Community Build will open a free earthquake assistance center that 
will offer preparedness and counseling services for homeowners affected by the 
January earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The center, at 3428 W. 43rd St., will target its services to homeowners in the 
area bounded by Adams Boulevard on the north, Manchester Avenue on the south, 
Crenshaw Boulevard on the west and Vermont Avenue on the east. 
</P>
<P>
 Services will include identifying disaster assistance programs, earthquake 
preparedness workshops, reviewing earthquake-related repair contracts, 
verifying contractors' licenses, bonds and workmanship, legal counseling; 
small-business loans and referrals, and in-home and office counseling. 
</P>
<P>
 The center is a joint venture of Community Build, a nonprofit corporation 
formed in 1992 to strengthen the economic infrastructure of the inner city, and 
Fannie Mae, a private financial services company that increases mortgage credit 
among low- and middle-income families. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 290-6560. 
</P>
