<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: CENTRAL: DOWNTOWN; CASINO NIGHT TO AID HOMELESS AGENCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The annual "Monte Carlo Night" fund-raising gala for the Chrysalis homeless 
assistance agency will be May 18 at the Biltmore Hotel, 506 S. Grand Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, which features an elaborate dinner buffet, casino games, celebrity 
dealers, entertainment and a silent auction, is one of two major fund-raising 
events for the Skid Row-based agency that helped 419 homeless people find full- 
or part-time jobs last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The 10-year-old agency at 516 S. Main St. provides assistance in all aspects 
of finding a job, from writing a resume, practicing for interviews and learning 
computer skills to advice on how to dress appropriately. 
</P>
<P>
 The agency also provides a place for homeless job applicants to receive phone 
calls and mail. 
</P>
<P>
 Chrysalis also operates the Labor Connection, a temp agency that contracts 
with local companies and industries for temporary work that can sometimes lead 
to permanent employment for the homeless. 
</P>
<P>
 Monte Carlo Nite, which typically brings in more than $150,000 for the agency, 
and an October run for the homeless account for half of Chrysalis' annual 
budget. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for the fund raiser, which begins at 6 p.m., are $75. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 895-7777. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
