<P>
YOUTH CENTER OPENING DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The opening of youth facilities at the Grand Olympic Auditorium have been 
delayed until the sports complex receives building permits to complete 
construction. 
</P>
<P>
 The newly refurbished Grand Olympic Sports Complex will house a boxing and 
fitness center for youths from the central city and was scheduled to open last 
month. 
</P>
<P>
 Boxing trainer Richard Allen, director of the Hoover Street Gym, is going to 
run the boxing program when the training gym and fitness center are completed. 
</P>
<P>
 "Everything has been delayed because of the earthquake," said Allen. "It's 
impossible to get a (building) inspector unless it's related to earthquake 
damage. I expect the gym to be open in June or early July." 
</P>
