<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMPETING NO BREEZE AT GOLDEN LEAGUE FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The rain that hit Southern California on Friday afternoon bypassed the Golden 
League track and field finals at Cerro Coso College in Ridgecrest, but 
inclement weather hampered performances. 
</P>
<P>
 The conditions -- 40-degree temperatures with wind gusts exceeding 40 m.p.h. 
-- were so bad that Jamaal Chase of Quartz Hill won the long jump and triple 
jump with distances of 19 feet 10 inches and 42-6 1/2.Chase has personal bests 
of 24-2 1/4 in the long jump and 49-3 in the triple jump. 
</P>
<P>
 Jerome Davis of Burroughs Ridgecrest, the proud owner of a 47.45-second best 
in the 400, won that event in 52.45. 
</P>
<P>
 Quartz Hill's Michelle Perry and Felicia Fletcher won the girls' long jump at 
15-5 and triple jump at 29-11 1/2. They have respective bests of 17-1 1/4 and 
33-10. 
</P>
<P>
 Quartz Hill co-coach Don Crimin said the elements were "the worst I've ever 
seen for this time of the year for a track meet." 
</P>
<P>
 "There were times when kids were almost stopped in their tracks in the middle 
of a race," he said. "The wind was that strong." JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</TEXT>
