<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CSUN ZEROES IN ON FRESNO WITH DOUBLEHEADER SWEEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge swept San Diego State, 2-0 and 7-0, Saturday in a Western 
Athletic Conference softball doubleheader in San Diego, setting up a WAC 
showdown with sixth-ranked Fresno State at Northridge next Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Against San Diego State (21-25-1, 4-16-1 in conference play), Amy Windmiller 
(21-2) pitched a two-hitter and struck out five in the opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Beth Calcante's run-scoring single and Tamara Ivie's sacrifice fly in the 
seventh accounted for the Matadors' runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Fourth-ranked Northridge (42-7, 17-3) pounded 11 hits in the second game, 
scoring four runs in the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Terri Pearson, Scia Maumausolo, Traci Gallian and Vicky Rios each had two 
hits.  
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore Jennifer Richardson (9-0) pitched a five-hitter and struck out five. 
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran 14, Whittier 3 -- The top-seeded Kingsmen breezed in their 
opening game of the Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Sam Arroyo (8-1) pitched seven innings, giving up five hits and an unearned 
run. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Fick and John Becker of Cal Lutheran (29-5-1) hit home runs on 
consecutive pitches in the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
 The Kingsmen will play host to third-seeded Pomona-Pitzer (22-12) at 1 p.m. 
today. 
</P>
<P>
 Desert 17, Antelope Valley 5 -- Chad Goodwin had two home runs for the 
Antelopes (14-19, 8-16) in a Foothill Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission 10, East L.A. 7 -- Francisco Flores hit a three-run homer in the ninth 
to lift the Free Spirit in a nonconference game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
