<HEADLINE>
<P>
OCC HOLDS OFF PIERCE FOR VOLLEYBALL TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Led by Dave Keller's 24 kills, Orange Coast beat stubborn Pierce College, 
16-14, 17-15, 15-13, Saturday at Santa Barbara City College to become the State 
men's volleyball champion. 
</P>
<P>
 Keller, along with Lance Perry (16 kills), proved to be the Pirates' primary 
offensive weapon. He kept the pressure on Pierce, which beat Orange Coast the 
last two times. 
</P>
<P>
 Perry was named most valuable player of the match and teammates Jason Crone 
and Mike Melcher made the all-tournament team. Gabe Higa led Pierce with 22 
kills. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast regains the championship after losing it in 1991. The Pirates 
finish the season 17-3. Pierce College ends its season 18-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
