<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAIN HALTS RACING AT SAUGUS, VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER and RON STAPP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For the second consecutive night, rain forced the cancellation of racing at 
Ventura Raceway. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday night's SCRA sprint car opener was called off by track management 45 
minutes before the scheduled 7 p.m. start when a light drizzle became a 
downpour. 
</P>
<P>
 It was only the third rainout in seven years at the 5/16-mile clay oval, the 
first coming last June, the second coming Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Friday's stock car program may be made up, but there are no plans to 
reschedule the sprint car program. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A threat of rain forced postponement of the Sportsman Championship Series at 
Saugus Speedway for the second time in three weeks.  
</P>
<P>
 Despite an apparent clearing in the storm, track officials postponed the races 
based on weather reports, and did so shortly after a car driven by sportsman 
Marty Stowell of Canyon Country collided with the wall in Turn 1 during 
qualifying. DARIN ESPER and RON STAPP 
</P>
</TEXT>
