<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; ALEMANY RALLY PULLS OUT A VICTORY THAT EARNS A SPOT IN 
PLAYOFFS, 14-12 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alemany High rallied from six runs down, scoring twice in the seventh inning 
to escape with a 14-12 Mission League victory over Loyola Saturday and clinch a 
spot in the Southern Section playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany (18-7, 9-3 in league play) is one game behind Notre Dame with two 
league games left. 
</P>
<P>
 The Indians trailed, 9-3, after three innings but a three-run home run by 
catcher Robbie Glenn and a six-run fifth inning gave them a 12-10 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart 7, Burbank 2 -- Luis Sanchez (6-1) pitched a three-hitter and faced only 
24 batters as the host Indians (18-4, 10-0) clinched the Foothill League title. 
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 THOUSAND OAKS TOURNAMENT 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 3, Lakewood 0 -- Sara Griffin (17-1) pitched a one-hitter, 
striking out nine and walking one for the Pioneers (21-1) in the final. 
</P>
<P>
 San Marcos 2, Newbury Park 0 -- Melissa Brecht's double in the seventh inning 
ended Jenny Hehnke's bid for a perfect game and was the only hit for the 
Panthers in the third-place game. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena 4, Thousand Oaks 0 -- Nichole Greathouse (7-1) allowed two hits in her 
fifth shutout of the year in the fifth-place game. 
</P>
